(firstQuint)Safety and Efficacy of CryoCor Cryoablation for PAF.

 The purpose of this prospective, randomized multi-center clinical study is to establish the benefits of the CryoCor(TM) Cardiac Cryoablation System for treating symptomatic paroxysmal atrial fibrillation (PAF) in comparison to treatment with anti-arrhythmic medications alone.

 This study also evaluates the safety profile of the CryoCor(TM) Cardiac Cryoablation System when used in this same setting.

